The Western Cape’s police officers appear to be ill-equipped to carry out the basic requirements of their jobs, according to the Police Needs and Priorities Report. It reveals 45.8% of 2,785 detectives haven’t been trained in the Basic Detective Learning Programme. eNCA's Monique Mortlock has the details on this story. #eNCA #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape’s police officers appear to be ill-equipped to carry out the basic requirements of their jobs, according to the Police Needs and Priorities Report. It reveals 45.8% of 2,785 detectives haven’t been trained in the Basic Detective Learning Programme. eNCA's Monique Mortlock has the details in the video above. #eNCA #DStv403